						               													<description>Mist is a trick-taking game for exactly 4 players using a standard deck of 52 cards, but for which you can see the suits on the rear of the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player's hand begins face down in front of them with a chip on it.  During the game, players can remove chips from their cards, 2 at a time, to look at their values; however, they must remember not to forget the value, as they cannot look at it again.  The chips which are removed in this way will be used as a player's bid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chips remaining on cards which are played to tricks form a pool which is given to the player who wins a trick.  Chips acquired in this way are used to convert a player's unplayed card to a trump card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most points after 4 rounds wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
